In order to build Wrapl/Riva, you will need the following programs/libraries:
1. Gcc:
	http://gcc.gnu.org
2. Omake:
	http://omake.metaprl.org
3: Boehm-Demers-Weiser conservative garbage collector:
	http://www.hpl.hp.com/personal/Hans_Boehm/gc/
4: GNU Multiple Precision Arithmetic Library (GMP):
	http://gmplib.org/
5: libConfuse:
	http://www.nongnu.org/confuse/
6: Lua:
	http://www.lua.org/

If you want to use the GTK+ binding (still in testing), you will also need:
7. GTK+:
	http://www.gtk.org/
